    Aneri Patel3 months ago on Google
    1/5
    I am not a picky traveler by any means, all I really care about is a clean room, decent breakfast, and air conditioning. However, this hotel was frankly disgusting. We checked in and noticed there were no towels in our room so we requested …
    I am not a picky traveler by any means, all I really care about is a clean room, decent breakfast, and air conditioning. However, this hotel was frankly disgusting. We checked in and noticed there were no towels in our room so we requested some and were even willing to go downstairs to grab them. We were told they’d be brought up in an hour so we decided to go to the beach and out for dinner in the meantime. When we came back five hours later the towels still weren’t delivered so we requested them again. The towels were brought up 30 minutes later and we immediately found make up stains all over them. Our bedding also had stains on it. We soon realized our air conditioning also wasn’t working so I called the front desk. Ten minutes later someone came to check it out, pressed a few buttons, and said it should work but will take time to cool the room down. The air didn’t work at all through out the night, and when we spoke with reception the following morning regarding a possible discount due to the fact that we were unable to sleep in our hot and humid room, they told us unfortunately nothing could be done because our card had already been charged upon check in. Breakfast was also disappointing. The food looked like it had been left out for days and the goat cheese tasted like it had expired. The bread was also stale so I decided to go with cereal assuming it was a safe choice. The cereal was extremely stale and very difficult to eat. I will say that the scrambled eggs and fresh oranges were delicious, however, the edible options stopped there. Overall, this was a very frustrating experience for a hotel that looks so beautiful from the outside.

    The Fredj Hotel & Spa is a 4-star hotel in Tangier, Morocco with full spa services that opened in August 2017. The downtown location is 42 Rue de Hollande, where the former Dawliz Hotel used to be until it closed about four years ago. After …
    The Fredj Hotel & Spa is a 4-star hotel in Tangier, Morocco with full spa services that opened in August 2017. The downtown location is 42 Rue de Hollande, where the former Dawliz Hotel used to be until it closed about four years ago. After it was sold, the hotel building was expanded and upgraded. Fredj Hotel & Spa is directly across the street from the historic Grand Hotel Villa de France.
    Fredj Hotel & Spa has large rooms and suites, all with comfortable beds, great bathrooms with lots of hot water, and air-conditioning.
    In addition, the hotel has two restaurants and upstairs there is a quiet cafe and restaurant with a spacious wraparound terrace that has incredible panoramic views of the port, the crescent-shaped beach, the marina, Tarifa, Spain and the mountains of Andalucia in the distance. No alcohol is served in the restaurant.
    The female receptionist at the Fredj spoke excellent English when I first visited the place. Prices in high season are about 1,600 Dirhams per night for a double (approximately $165), but the prices are lower during the off-season.

    About this hotel

    Offering views of the ancient Medina and the Mediterranean Sea, this upscale hotel is 2 km from the Kasbah Museum and 6 km from Park Alrmelat. Tangier Ibn Battuta Airport is 13 km away. …

    The warmly decorated rooms offer flat-screen TVs, free Wi-Fi, and minibars, as well as tea and coffeemaking facilities, sitting areas, desks and safes; some have balconies and/or sea views. Suites add fireplaces, living rooms. and whirlpool tubs. Family rooms are available.

    Parking is complimentary. Other amenities include a spa, a hammam and an outdoor pool, plus a warm piano bar and an airy restaurant with sea and city views.
